---
// GTM Open Source Section - Emphasize the open-source advantage
// Key Daytona strategy element: transparency builds trust
---

<section class="opensource">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="content-grid">
      <div class="content-left">
        <div class="section-label">Open Source</div>
        <h2>Audit the Code.<br />Trust the Tool.</h2>
        <p class="description">
          Every line of Caro is open source under AGPL-3.0. You can audit the safety patterns, verify the local-only architecture, and contribute improvements. No black boxes. No mystery about what runs on your machine.
        </p>

        <div class="benefits">
          <div class="benefit">
            <span class="benefit-icon">üîç</span>
            <div class="benefit-content">
              <h4>Fully Auditable</h4>
              <p>Review every safety pattern, every line of inference code. Know exactly what you're running.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="benefit">
            <span class="benefit-icon">üîß</span>
            <div class="benefit-content">
              <h4>Community-Driven</h4>
              <p>Report issues, suggest features, contribute code. The roadmap is shaped by users, not investors.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="benefit">
            <span class="benefit-icon">üöÄ</span>
            <div class="benefit-content">
              <h4>Fork Freely</h4>
              <p>Build your own version, add custom safety patterns, integrate with your toolchain. It's your tool.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <a href="https://github.com/wildcard/caro" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="github-cta">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
